title: For Sale:  DTA SRS-A1 Rifle Chassis 338 LAPUA
location: San Francisco - East Bay, San Francisco, California
postcontent:
I put a big down payment for this rifle, but due to my financial situation, i am not able to purchase the rifle at this time.  I am willing to give you my down payment, if you are interested in purchasing the rifle from the dealer. all you have to do is show up at the gun dealer and take over my purchase, and you can keep my down payment as part of your payment. the dealer will accept cash or credit card as long as you come in person.

Just a heads up, this is a special edition rifle that was produced for shot show 2015, so it has the OD GREEN finish. you cannot get this color anymore.

The Stealth Recon Scout A1 (SRS-A1) is the most versatile Sniper Rifle system in the world. It is nearly a foot shorter than conventional sniper rifles, maintains 1/2 MOA or better accuracy with DTM Ammunition, and can be easily adapted to individual mission requirements by changing the weapon’s caliber and length. Whether a police sniper is shooting 50 yards or a military sniper is shooting a mile the SRS offers unrivaled flexibility in a package shorter than the M16 battle rifle. 

Accuracy
The SRS achieves superb accuracy in all calibers because it's built around core accuracy components:

1. Match grade (free-floated) barrels, chambers, and crowns
2. High quality match trigger
3. Solid, repeating return-to-zero barrel mounting system (the receiver securely clamps around the first six inches of barrel)

Quick Caliber Conversion
The SRS is quickly convertible between the following calibers: .308 Winchester (22" and 26" barrels), .260 Remington, 6.5x47 Lapua, 7mm Winchester Short Mag, .300 Winchester Magnum, .338 Norma Magnum, and .338 Lapua Magnum. The caliber conversion and return to zero is simple and takes less than 60 seconds.
Benefits:
1. Operators can change rifle length, penetration, and distance capabilities.
2. Snipers can shoot various ammo calibers and types depending on METT-T.
3. Snipers can progressively train on more powerful ammo.
4. Reduced training costs (train and practice with .308 WIN)
5. Reduced system down-times (the operator can change his own barrels).

Compact
The SRS is the shortest purpose-built sniper rifle in the world. The telescoping bolt and bullpup configuration make it almost a foot shorter than conventional Mauser-style turnbolt sniper rifles. The compact design shifts weight and center-of-gravity rearward, creating a perfectly balanced and relatively short sniper rifle.

Rugged
The SRS was designed to operate under the harshest conditions and abuse. It is built of high-impact polymers; aircraft grade aluminum (ANSI 7075-T6); ultra high-strength steels; and some of the most durable coatings known to man. The monolithic receiver serves as a full length mounting chassis, eliminating the need for any sort of receiver-to-stock bedding interface. Ergonomic stock panels attach directly to the receiver.
The SRS maintains its accuracy and reliability in virtually any environment, including subzero arctic temperatures, extreme desert heat and dust, and wet jungle environments.

title: For Sale:  GG&G A2 Flip Up Rear Sight w/ Locking Detent (BUIS)
postcontent:
The GG&G A2 Style BUIS (Back Up Iron Sight) provides the operator with an easy-to-install and easy-to-operate flip up rear sight, and includes an important locking detent. Once placed in the up position, the sight cannot be folded down without depressing the spring assisted detent release button located on the left side of the sight base. This totally eliminates the possibility of accidentally lowering the sight. The A2 BUIS can be used as a co-witness iron sight with most of the red dot sighting systems. This sight features the standard A2-style double peep aperture and has full windage adjustment. It uses the Colt-style windage knob and windage screw. One click of the windage knob provides approximately 0.48 MOA change when mounted on the M16A2E4 rifle and about 0.65 MOA on the M4 carbine.  When in the down position, it will clear most optics. The A2 BUIS mount body and sight stem are manufactured from 6061 T6 aluminum and black hard-coat anodized per mil spec. 
I prefer a cash-only FTF in the Highlands Ranch area but I am willing to ship. No trades. Please include a phone# with your email if you are a serious buyer. I can send more pictures if you need them. 
 I will also ship this for anyone seeing this ad out-of-state (or anywhere not close enough for a FTF). The buyer will pay for shipping and handling. I will take PayPal, money orders or personal checks as payment. If using a check I will deposit it first to make sure it clears and then I will send the item.

title: For Sale:  Intratec Tec-22 Scorpion Threaded Semi-22 Fun from 80s/90s
postcontent: An excellent example of the Tec-9's little brother. These designs came about in the 80s (actually in the 70s when Intratec was Interdynamics and they made open bolt semis banned in 1981) when gun designs were fun and practical. Yes, this is too large for a concealable handgun and not a target pistol and it is 22, so not the best choice for defense....though with a 50 round mag/drum holding a full box in the pistol, it would be a hell of a deterant. So what is the purpose of this one? Fun! Plinking a box of 22s at the range or outdoors if you are fortunate to have land. A threaded barrel makes attaching a registered supressor easy or one of the many attachments made for this gun like extended barrels with slotted covers that give you a grip in front. Many of these were beat up over the years and the top cover is stamped steel and the lower section polymer. This one is in excellent condition with only one cosmetic mark on the barrel from storing it in a case with those silica pacs touching the barrel. Made a lighter area half the area of a dime. The bolt/firing pin/spring is all one unit and this pin is straight and like new. Replacements are cheap as are all parts for these, but this one is tip-top shape. Comes with the original Intratec 20 round mag which fits tight and is 100% reliable (these prefer round nose to many hollow-points and high-velocity is better) though any 10-50 round Ruger 10-22 magazine which are among the most common and lowest cost mags will fit in this. Big enough that in 22 there is no rise or recoil so you can fire off 30 rounds or 50 as fast as your finger works and stay on the can bouncing along the ground. I can nail empty 12 gauge shells tossed out on the ground too. Many of these tripled during the last "panic" and sure to happen again. This is priced well towards the bottom of the range of all listed guns so you will ALWAYS be able to resell it for the same or more if you take care of it. I can work direct with Florida residents with a valid CWP (that ensures age and no felon status) or will ship to FFL for $35. (Handguns cost more to ship) $289 for a threaded barrel version in super condition is a great price..check all the usual sites and compare
